# Migrate to OpenStreetMap Data Source

The project currently has code to fetch from OpenTripMap (via [build_db.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/build_db.py) and [data_gyumri.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/data_gyumri.py) fallbacks) and an experimental script to fetch from OpenStreetMap (OSM) via [openstreetmap_collect_gyumri.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/openstreetmap/openstreetmap_collect_gyumri.py). To complete the migration to OSM as the sole data source, we need to remove all OTM-specific code, update [build_db.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/build_db.py) to fetch from OSM, and clean up [data_gyumri.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/data_gyumri.py).

## Proposed Changes

### Database Generation
Update the database building script to completely rely on the Overpass API for OpenStreetMap content.
#### [MODIFY] [build_db.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/build_db.py)
Replace the OpenTripMap API calls with the OpenStreetMap Overpass API queries (based on the logic in [openstreetmap_collect_gyumri.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/openstreetmap/openstreetmap_collect_gyumri.py)). The script will generate the primary [places_gyumri.json](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/places_gyumri.json) file populated entirely with OSM data.
#### [DELETE] [openstreetmap_collect_gyumri.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/openstreetmap/openstreetmap_collect_gyumri.py)
This script can be fully removed since [build_db.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/build_db.py) will subsume its responsibilities.

### Data Access Logic
Clean up data loading to rely only on the OSM format.
#### [MODIFY] [data_gyumri.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/data_gyumri.py)
- Simplify `candidates` in [_load_places](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/data_gyumri.py#10-36) to default properly to [places_gyumri.json](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/places_gyumri.json).
- Remove legacy OTM formatting checks and fallbacks (e.g., the `if isinstance(tags, dict)` branches that fallback to OTM structure).

## Verification Plan
### Automated Verification
- We will execute `python build_db.py` to test that the OSM Overpass API query succeeds and properly persists [places_gyumri.json](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/places_gyumri.json).
- We will create and run a scratch script (`/tmp/test.py`) that imports [data_gyumri.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/data_gyumri.py) and calls [get_nearby_places(lat=40.7894, lon=43.8475)](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/data_gyumri.py#54-131) to ensure that parsing and formatting operations over the new OSM data return correct results without exceptions.
